   Makes Public Offering
   Of 6.4 Million Shares
</HL>
<DATE>
07/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CNNR
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Conner Peripherals Inc. said it made a
public offering to sell 6.4 million shares of common stock,
at $26.75 a share. Prior to the stock offer, Conner had 41.8
million common shares outstanding.
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Conner
closed at $27.75, up $1.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Conner designs, makes and sells computer disk drives.
   Of the shares offered, six million were sold by the
company and certain shareholders sold 400,000. The company
said 5.1 million shares were sold in the U.S. and 1.3 million
in Europe.
   Proceeds will be used principally to expand and improve
manufacturing capacity world-wide and to provide working
capital for general corporate purposes.
