<IN>
SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)
</IN>
<LP>
   CHICAGO -- The Chicago Board Options Exchange named former
Securities and Exchange Commission Chairman John Shad a
public director of the exchange.
   The CBOE has four such directors on its 21-member board.
Each public director serves a two-year term.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In 1989, Mr. Shad became chairman of Drexel Burnham
Lambert Group Inc.'s board and oversight committee, which is
responsible for assuring the firm complies with its consent
agreements with the SEC and the Justice Department.
</TEXT>
