<HL>
   Marketing &amp; Media:
   American Banker Editor,
   Fred R. Bleakley, Resigns
</HL>
<DATE>
07/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS T.TOC
</CO>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Fred R. Bleakley resigned as editor of
American Banker, a daily newspaper owned by Thomson
Publishing Corp.
   Mr. Bleakley, a former deputy business editor of the New
York Times, said he resigned because of a disagreement with
George W. Landgrebe, president of American Banker, who had
hired Mr. Bleakley. "George and I couldn't reach agreement on
my proposal to report directly to him," Mr. Bleakley said. "I
wasn't comfortable with other executives getting involved."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Bleakley had been editor since April 1989, when he was
hired to thoroughly redesign the paper.
   A successor to Mr. Bleakley wasn't named and executives of
Thomson Publishing couldn't be reached for comment.
</TEXT>
