<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report:
                                                                                                       

                          CORPORATE
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sumitomo Bank International Finance N.V. -- $500 million
of 9.55% guaranteed notes due July 15, 2000, priced at 99.972
to yield 9.554%. The noncallable notes were priced at a
spread of 1.02 percentage points above the Treasury's 10-year
note. Rated double-A-1 by Moody's Investors Service Inc. and
double-A by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., the issue will be sold
through underwriters led by Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co.
   Williams Cos. -- $150 million of 10 1/4% debentures due
