priced at 1.72 percentage points above the Treasury's 30-year
bond. Rated Baa-3 by Moody's and triple-B by S&amp;P, the issue
will be sold through underwriters led by First Boston Corp.
                                                                                                       

                          MUNICIPAL
                                                                                                       

   Phoenix, Ariz. -- the bulk of a $117.6 million issue of
bonds, including $72.6 million of general obligation bonds,
due July 1, 1991-2006, 2010 and 2014 and $45 million of
street and highway user revenue bonds, Series 1990, due July
1, 1991-2006, 2009 and 2010, were seen won by a J.P. Morgan
Securities Inc. group. The firm apparently won the $72.6
million of general obligation bonds with a bid setting the
true interest cost at 6.95%. The bonds, rated double-A by
Moody's and double-A-plus by S&amp;P, were priced for reoffering
to yield from 5.90% in 1991 to 7.05% in 2014. Current
interest serial bonds are priced for reoffering to yield from
5.90% in 1991 to 7.00% in 2006. There are $12.3 million of
term bonds due in 2010 that weren't formally reoffered. There
are $8.3 million of 6% term bonds priced at 87.94 to yield
7.05% in 2014. The remainder of the deal, $45 million of
street and highway user revenue bonds, were apparently won by
a Clayton Brown &amp; Associates Inc. group, with a bid setting
the true interest cost at 7.08%. The bonds, rated single-A-1
by Moody's and double-A by S&amp;P, were priced for reoffering to
yield from 6.00% in 1991 to 7.20% in 2010. Current interest
serial bonds are priced to yield from 6.00% in 1991 to 7.05%
in 2006. There are $12.8 million of 6.50% term bonds priced
at 93.80 to yield 7.10% in 2009. There are $4.7 million of 7
1/8% term bonds priced at 99.21 to yield 7.20% in 2010.
                                                                                                       

