<LP>
   Dixons Group PLC of Britain, a consumer electronics
retailer, said pretax profit for the year ended April 28 rose
2.2% to #80.1 million ($145.9 million) from #78.4 million a
year earlier, as advances in British retailing offset a
decline in U.S. earnings.
   The results, slightly exceeding market expectations and
Dixons' own estimate, are the first since the government in
May blocked a #461 million bid for Dixons by Kingfisher PLC,
a British retailer, on the ground that the acquisition would
have been anti-competitive.
