<LP>
   Suedzucker AG of West Germany, a sugar company, said
profit for the year ended Feb. 28 rose 48% to 86.2 million
marks ($52.4 million), or 40 marks a share, from 58.2 million
marks, or 28.20 marks a share, a year earlier.
   Sales rose 33% to 3.6 billion marks from 2.7 billion
marks. Suedzucker said its 1.35 billion-mark acquisition of
the Belgian sugar company Raffinerie Tirlemontois S.A. last
year, which made Suedzucker Europe's largest sugar producer,
boosted sales in the last five months of fiscal 1990.
</LP>
