   The company plans to raise its dividend 27% to 14 marks a
share from 11 marks.
   Analysts had criticized the high price paid for
Tirlemontois, saying Suedzucker was primarily interested in
acquiring the company's sugar production quotas. Each
European Community country has a production quota, and the EC
support price is well above the market level. Last November,
Suedzucker officials conceded the price was high, citing the
quotas. The company will eventually lower its holding in
wholly owned Tirlemontois to about 60%.
